A day I remember lost friends

column1: Re: Temp profile- DO data and drop in Secchi on 11/12.....It is obvious that the lake is turning over.

column2: Water clearing rapidly as zooplankton population explodes and lake stratification robs the surface of phosphorous. Note the P concentration dropping from 20 to 7 between mid-April and mid-June.
Typical spring clearing in full swing. See http://www.blackoaklake.com/Documents/Secchigraphs-multi-yeargraphs.xls for graphs of the last nine seasons.
OAT 67F- WIND 2710- LEVEL 4.75"- SHALLOW WATER TEMP 71F
OAT 80F- WIND 1805- 20% CLOUD COVER- SHALLOW WATER TEMP 77F
OAT 72F- WIND 2907- SHALLOW WATER TEMP 71F  Another "No Detect" for Phosphorous. Just as on June 24- 2010- the P level was so low it couldn't be detected.
OAT 51F- WIND 2907- Shallow Water Temp 61F OAT 51F- WIND 2907- Shallow Water Temp 61F
Overcast- OAT 60F- Wind Calm.   Ice out today- the third latest in our 105 years of recorded ice out dates. Conductivity 42uS.
OAT 62F- WIND 2807- POST TURNOVER RAPID CLEARING UNDERWAY AS ZOOPLANKTON POPULATION EXPLODES.
Water continues clearing with the expanding zooplankton population.
Clarity starting to decrease per seasonal norms. See http://www.blackoaklake.com/Documents/BOL_Secchi_'02-'12.xlsx.
Surface water temp today is at 45F and it appears that fall turnover is underway.
Latest Secchis show that we are well into fall turnover
MERRY CHRISTMAS TO MY FELLOW CLMN VOLUNTEERS!!!!!!!!!!
Ice-out was 05/12; Surface water temp was 48.4F. Conductivity was 32uS. Greenish cast to water due to algae bloom from spring turnover. The zooplankton are on their way!

Finally- the Secchi seems to be following the historical trend of late summer. Water is a beautiful deep blue. The rapidly rising water level (two feet in one year!) seems to be the reason for our decreased Secchi as it inundates 7 drought years worth of mostly terrestrial plants causing a jump in our Chlorophyll over previous years.
We are already well into fall turnover. Secchi is tanking and the water has a greenish cast to it.
OAT 52F- Wind Calm- Fall turnover well underway.
Ice-Out April 20........6 days earlier than the 107 year recorded average.
Lowest Secchi of the year right after ice-out
Secchi continues poor as cold weather delays lake stratification.
Aileron helped.  Our Secchi continues to improve as the lake stratifies (see Temp profile above).
Late June TP and Chl sample sent in today.
Clear skies- OAT 72F- Wind 1810- Conductivity 43mS  CLR- OAT 72F- Wind 1810- Conductivity 43 umhos/cm
Thermocline moving down in this late summertime.
Turnover has begun....Secchi has dropped and water has a greenish hue to it. OAT 62F- WIND 2705- Conductivity 33 umhos.
Ice-out was on April 22- four days earlier than the April 26 average of our 108 years of recorded ice-out dates. Loons already on the lake yodeling!
Water taking on a greenish hue and a decreasing Secchi ..... typical of pre-stratification.
Ice out was April 15. Water level the highest since 2006.
Water level very high. We're up 6+" since ice-out on April 15 and up over 40" (yep- 40") since 2012. Clarity has taken a hit from the inundation of so much once terrestrial frontage.

Secchi has taken a big hit from this unusually high water. The water is the highest in decades having recently gone up 11" just since ice-out on April 15- 2017. Many years of exposed shoreline had grown a lot of terrestrial plant life which has now been washed back into the lake.
Highest water in decades has heavily impacted our clarity. Level now up 45" since 2012 and a full foot since ice-out April 15.......its driving the dock guys crazy!
Ice-out was May 12- 16 days after the 100 year average of April 26. Water level at modern record high with lots of flotsam in the lake.

column1: Water level continues to be highest in decades with old trees dead around newly flooded shoreline frontage.

column2: Clarity increasing nicely. Still highest water in many decades is killing many shoreline trees- some very old.
Looks like turnover is getting started.
Ice-out May 6- 10 days later than our 110 year average. Extremely high water.....up 54" over the last 8 years!
Water still very high with lots of flotsam.
Highest water ever. We are now 54 inches above the near record low in 2012. Lots of flotsam now in the lake and clarity has been adversely affected as well.
Flotsam everywhere as water level continues high.
Lake still near record high. Secchis coming up nicely.....finally!
Water still at record highs eroding shoreline trees and hills.
